1
00:00:06,341 --> 00:00:11,031
Chekhov says in one of his plays
describing one man,

2
00:00:11,051 --> 00:00:14,040
“He was a simple man. 
A stupid man.”

3
00:00:14,190 --> 00:00:16,636
[Simple-Hearted or Simpleton]

4
00:00:16,636 --> 00:00:21,453
So, there’s simple-hearted 
and simpleton.

5
00:00:21,734 --> 00:00:32,969
So someone who is interested 
to advance spiritually,

6
00:00:33,601 --> 00:00:34,446
we’re told,

7
00:00:34,446 --> 00:00:38,449
hṛdayenabhyanujñāto
yo dharmas taṁ nibhodhata
[Ms: 2.01]

8
00:00:38,449 --> 00:00:40,678
they will factor in that,

9
00:00:40,678 --> 00:00:44,630
“I have a strong tendency 
towards self-deception;

10
00:00:44,630 --> 00:00:48,766
I can see it in my life, 
in my circumstances.

11
00:00:48,766 --> 00:00:51,045
So, knowing that I have
a tendency to do that,

12
00:00:51,045 --> 00:00:55,445
let this not be 
another example of that—

13
00:00:55,445 --> 00:00:58,131
my making spiritual connections.”

14
00:00:58,131 --> 00:01:03,660
So then we have to look
into tradition, lineage, etc.

15
00:01:03,660 --> 00:01:08,643
Gandhi, 
when the British were there,

16
00:01:08,855 --> 00:01:17,614
he realised that khādī
(the cloth made by the charkha

17
00:01:17,614 --> 00:01:20,575
and from the cotton, 
and the weavers, by hand),

18
00:01:20,575 --> 00:01:22,841
every aspect of it is hand;

19
00:01:22,841 --> 00:01:24,754
he thought, 
“This is good for India.

20
00:01:24,754 --> 00:01:26,096
It’s good for the people 
in the villages;

21
00:01:26,096 --> 00:01:27,187
it’s good for the country.

22
00:01:27,187 --> 00:01:29,728
So if you believe in India, 
just buy khādī;

23
00:01:29,728 --> 00:01:34,590
don’t buy the factory 
mill cloth of the British.”

24
00:01:34,590 --> 00:01:37,382
So a movement started growing.

25
00:01:37,382 --> 00:01:39,428
But then—the British 
are very clever;

26
00:01:39,428 --> 00:01:42,513
in their factory they learned 
how to produce cloth

27
00:01:42,513 --> 00:01:47,853
that looks like khādī.
So they started selling it.

28
00:01:47,853 --> 00:01:53,676
So this led him to establish 
the Khādī Saṅgha.

29
00:01:54,276 --> 00:01:57,121
It’s still there in Kolkata, 
and other places you can find.

30
00:01:57,121 --> 00:01:58,928
—[Swāmī Avadhūt] “I bought 
some stuff there.” 
—“Yes.”

31
00:01:58,928 --> 00:02:01,424
So the Khādī Saṅgha … 
And what he was saying,

32
00:02:01,424 --> 00:02:05,413
“We’re starting an association, 
us, who really know

33
00:02:05,413 --> 00:02:07,509
what khādī is 
in the pure state,

34
00:02:07,509 --> 00:02:10,425
it will have our stamp 
and our seal on it.

35
00:02:10,425 --> 00:02:14,295
If it does not have the stamp 
and seal of the Khādī Saṅgha,

36
00:02:14,295 --> 00:02:17,539
it’s counterfeit, 
it’s not the real thing.”

37
00:02:19,292 --> 00:02:23,430
So, in something as serious 
as spiritual culture,

38
00:02:23,430 --> 00:02:26,391
someone’s going to have
to invest some time,

39
00:02:26,391 --> 00:02:28,893
some energy, 
do some research,

40
00:02:28,893 --> 00:02:32,355
but ultimately, what Manu says, 
and what I quoted,

41
00:02:32,355 --> 00:02:33,899
yo dharmas taṁ nibho …

42
00:02:33,899 --> 00:02:36,945
hṛdayenabhyanujñāto 
yo dharmas taṁ nibhodhata—
[Ms: 2.01]

43
00:02:36,945 --> 00:02:39,905
ultimately it’s an affair 
of the heart.

44
00:02:39,905 --> 00:02:41,781
And now 
we’re back to that point:

45
00:02:41,781 --> 00:02:44,258
simple-hearted or simpleton?

46
00:02:44,258 --> 00:02:49,424
Self-deceiver or sincere, 
earnest hankering for the truth?

47
00:02:49,424 --> 00:02:52,757
So Śrīla Guru Mahārāj
has an aphorism

48
00:02:52,757 --> 00:02:56,758
that actually 
applies to everything,

49
00:02:56,758 --> 00:03:01,969
including all the varieties 
of theistic culture

50
00:03:01,969 --> 00:03:04,263
that you could 
possibly conceive.

51
00:03:04,263 --> 00:03:08,648
Everything is included 
within this one sūtra-like expression

52
00:03:08,664 --> 00:03:10,424
in which he says,

53
00:03:10,424 --> 00:03:15,795
“According to the inner 
sincere hankering of your heart

54
00:03:15,795 --> 00:03:20,413
you will come in connection 
with a particular level

55
00:03:20,413 --> 00:03:26,677
of theistic conception 
and subsequent association—

56
00:03:26,677 --> 00:03:30,538
that’s guaranteed.” 
So then what we’re left with is,

57
00:03:30,538 --> 00:03:36,295
“Oh! Then as long as I’m sincere, 
everything will be all-right.

58
00:03:36,295 --> 00:03:40,341
As long as I’m sincere, 
I’ll make the right choice.

59
00:03:40,341 --> 00:03:43,718
As long as I’m sincere, 
ultimately I’ll get there.”

60
00:03:43,718 --> 00:03:46,361
And that’s again grounded 
in the Gīta,

61
00:03:46,361 --> 00:03:48,246
where Kṛṣṇa tells Arjuna,

62
00:03:48,246 --> 00:03:51,685
na hi kalyāṇa-kṛt kaśchid 
durgatiṁ tāta gachchhati
[Bg: 6.40]

63
00:03:51,685 --> 00:03:55,295
which Guru Mahārāj 
renders sometimes as

64
00:03:56,003 --> 00:03:58,858
“The sincere will be victorious”

65
00:03:58,858 --> 00:04:02,163
or “Sincerity is invincible.”

